Step 1: Identify the required values from the statement.
• Net Profit = -1,401,436.89  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -4,398,760.38  

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio using the formula:
  Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)

Step 3: Since both Net Cash Flow and Net Profit are negative, the ratio will be positive:
  Ratio = (-4,398,760.38) / (-1,401,436.89) ≈ 3.14

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is approximately 3.14.

